acPerfMediaServices.description: This MIB defines the enterprise-specific objects needed to support performance management of the AudioCodes product. Performance measurements are grouped into the following MIB trees: acPerfIvr - performance measurements related to the IVR service acPerfBct - performance measurements related to the BCT service acPerfConf - performance measurements related to the Conferencing service acPerfTt - performance measurements related to the Test Trunk service

acPerfIvrPlayRequests.name: acPerfIvrPlayRequests
acPerfIvrPlayRequests.description: The total number of announcement requests received from the call agent. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlaySuccessful.name: acPerfIvrPlaySuccessful
acPerfIvrPlaySuccessful.description: Number of announcement requests processed successfully. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayFailedDueToLackOfResources.name: acPerfIvrPlayFailedDueToLackOfResources
acPerfIvrPlayFailedDueToLackOfResources.description: Number of announcement requests which failed to be played because some resource was not available. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayInProgress.name: acPerfIvrPlayInProgress
acPerfIvrPlayInProgress.description: The number of announcement operations that are currently in progress. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayDuration.name: acPerfIvrPlayDuration
acPerfIvrPlayDuration.description: The duration, in seconds, of all successful announcement requests. The average duration of all requests (average hold time) can be computed by dividing acPerfPlayDuration by acPerfPlaySuccessful. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayFailedDueToProvMismatch.name: acPerfIvrPlayFailedDueToProvMismatch
acPerfIvrPlayFailedDueToProvMismatch.description: Number of announcement requests which failed because of a provisioning mismatch. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayCollectRequests.name: acPerfIvrPlayCollectRequests
acPerfIvrPlayCollectRequests.description: The number of play collect requests. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayCollectSuccessful.name: acPerfIvrPlayCollectSuccessful
acPerfIvrPlayCollectSuccessful.description: Number of play collects completed successfully. A request is considered successful if the entire sequence, from initial prompt to success/failure prompt, is played out without a failure due to lack of resources, provisioning mismatch, or any other media server failure. The failure of the user to enter the proper digits is not a reason for failure of the request. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayCollectFailedDueToLackOfRes.name: acPerfIvrPlayCollectFailedDueToLackOfResources
acPerfIvrPlayCollectFailedDueToLackOfRes.description: The number of play collect requests that failed due to lack of resources. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayCollectFailedDueToProvMisma.name: acPerfIvrPlayCollectFailedDueToProvMismatch
acPerfIvrPlayCollectFailedDueToProvMisma.description: The number of play collect requests that failed due a provisioning mismatch. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayCollectInProgress.name: acPerfIvrPlayCollectInProgress
acPerfIvrPlayCollectInProgress.description: The number of play collect operations that are currently in progress. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrPlayCollectDuration.name: acPerfIvrPlayCollectDuration
acPerfIvrPlayCollectDuration.description: The duration, in seconds, of all successful play collect requests. The average duration of all requests can be computed by dividing acPlayCollectDuration by acPlayCollectSuccessful. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrContDigitCollectRequests.name: acPerfIvrContDigitCollectRequests
acPerfIvrContDigitCollectRequests.description: The number of continuous digit collect requests. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrContDigitCollectSuccessful.name: acPerfIvrContDigitCollectSuccessful
acPerfIvrContDigitCollectSuccessful.description: Number of continuous digit collects completed successfully. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrContDigitCollectFailedDueToLack.name: acPerfIvrContDigitCollectFailedDueToLackOfResources
acPerfIvrContDigitCollectFailedDueToLack.description: The number of continuous digit collect requests that failed due to lack of resources. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrContDigitCollectInProgress.name: acPerfIvrContDigitCollectInProgress
acPerfIvrContDigitCollectInProgress.description: The number of continuous digit collect operations that are currently in progress. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfIvrContDigitCollectDuration.name: acPerfIvrContDigitCollectDuration
acPerfIvrContDigitCollectDuration.description: The duration, in seconds, of all successful continuous digit collect requests. The average duration of all requests can be computed by dividing acDCCollectDuration by acDCCollectSuccessful. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfBctRequests.name: acPerfBctRequests
acPerfBctRequests.description: The total number of BCT contexts opened since the media server initialized Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfBctSuccessful.name: acPerfBctSuccessful
acPerfBctSuccessful.description: Number of BCT requests processed successfully. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfBctFailedDueToLackOfResources.name: acPerfBctFailedDueToLackOfResources
acPerfBctFailedDueToLackOfResources.description: Number of BCT requests which failed to be played because some resource was not available. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfBctInProgress.name: acPerfBctInProgress
acPerfBctInProgress.description: The number of BCT calls that are currently in progress. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfBctDuration.name: acPerfBctDuration
acPerfBctDuration.description: The duration, in seconds, of all successful BCT contexts. The average duration of all contexts can be computed by dividing acPerfBCTDuration by acPerfBCTSuccessful. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfBctTotalParticipants.name: acPerfBctTotalParticipants
acPerfBctTotalParticipants.description: The total number of BCT participants since the media server initialized Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfBctCurrentNumberOfParticipants.name: acPerfBctCurrentNumberOfParticipants
acPerfBctCurrentNumberOfParticipants.description: The number of participants in all BCT calls that are currently in progress. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfRequests.name: acPerfConfRequests
acPerfConfRequests.description: The total number of conferences processed since the last application restart. This is the number of conferences created and not the number of members. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfSuccessful.name: acPerfConfSuccessful
acPerfConfSuccessful.description: Number of conference requests processed successfully. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfInProgress.name: acPerfConfInProgress
acPerfConfInProgress.description: The number of conferences currently in progress. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfDuration.name: acPerfConfDuration
acPerfConfDuration.description: The duration, in seconds, of all successful conference requests. The average duration of all requests can be computed by dividing acPerfConfDuration by acPerfConfSuccessful. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfFailedDueToLackOfResources.name: acPerfConfFailedDueToLackOfResources
acPerfConfFailedDueToLackOfResources.description: The number of times a conference request was rejected due to lack of resources since the last application restart. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfAddRequests.name: acPerfConfAddRequests
acPerfConfAddRequests.description: The number of requests to add a conferee to an existing conference. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfAddSuccessful.name: acPerfConfAddSuccessful
acPerfConfAddSuccessful.description: The number of times a conferee was added successfuly to an existing conference. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfAddFailedDueToLackOfResources.name: acPerfConfAddFailedDueToLackOfResources
acPerfConfAddFailedDueToLackOfResources.description: The number of times a conferee could not be added to an existing conference due to a lack of resources. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfPortsUsed.name: acPerfConfPortsUsed
acPerfConfPortsUsed.description: The total number of ports that were reserved for conferences since the last application restart. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfConfPortsReserved.name: acPerfConfPortsReserved
acPerfConfPortsReserved.description: The number of conference ports currently reserved. This includes play ports, monitor ports and regular conferee ports. A monitor port may be reserved by the call agent when setting up a conference. The monitor port can then be used by one or more listen-only conferees. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfTtRequests.name: acPerfTtRequests
acPerfTtRequests.description: The number of test trunk calls requested. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfTtSuccessful.name: acPerfTtSuccessful
acPerfTtSuccessful.description: The number of test trunk calls that were successfully setup and torn down. This PM is not a reflection on whether the test actually passed or failed. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfTtInProgress.name: acPerfTtInProgress
acPerfTtInProgress.description: The number of test trunk calls that are currently in progress. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfTtDuration.name: acPerfTtDuration
acPerfTtDuration.description: The duration, in seconds, of all successful test trunk requests. This number is The time between a test trunk call being initiated and completed. The average duration of all requests can be computed by dividing acPerfTtDuration by acPerfTtSuccessful. Products: IPmedia 2000

acPerfTtFailedDueToLackOfResources.name: acPerfTtFailedDueToLackOfResources
acPerfTtFailedDueToLackOfResources.description: The number of times a test trunk request was rejected due to lack of resources since the last application restart. Products: IPmedia 2000
